and he still hasn't shown his face either.

271
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:49,400
Or maybe…

272
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:53,680
<i>Geun-il-nat-seo!</i>

273
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:57,640
Yong,

274
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:00,200
what's wrong?

275
00:32:00,280 --> 00:32:03,040
You're just some thug from a gambling den,

276
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:09,520
and you still dare compare yourself to me?

277
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:15,080
And you're trying to claim my sister too?

278
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:17,880
Over my dead body.

279
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:25,880
You sure are possessive of your sister.

280
00:32:26,840 --> 00:32:29,680
Almost like you're jealous.

281
00:32:30,280 --> 00:32:32,840
Good. You like that, don't you?

282
00:32:36,280 --> 00:32:37,320
Stand up straight.

283
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:49,640
Get up.

284
00:32:52,120 --> 00:32:53,760
- Wait.
- He's beating Wayu up.

285
00:32:53,840 --> 00:32:55,200
Can't you see that?

286
00:32:55,280 --> 00:32:58,880
I see it. And I also see
that Wayu hasn't signaled for help.

287
00:33:03,080 --> 00:33:04,360
He must have a plan.

288
00:33:05,160 --> 00:33:07,960
Wayu isn't stupid. Calm down.

289
00:33:13,800 --> 00:33:14,960
How's that?

290
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:18,360
Stop.

291
00:33:18,440 --> 00:33:20,080
Stop right now.

292
00:33:20,160 --> 00:33:23,280
Stop. Wayu. Wayu.

293
00:33:29,880 --> 00:33:32,080
What did Wayu do?
Why did you have to hurt him?

294
00:33:32,160 --> 00:33:33,600
He didn't do anything to me.

295
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:36,400
But he's trying to do something to you.

296
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:38,520
Ever since he came into our lives,

297
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,920
our family has had nothing but disaster.

298
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:42,680
You're the one causing the disaster.

299
00:33:44,600 --> 00:33:46,160
Wayu has never done anything to me.

300
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:48,560
So you dare defend him now?

301
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:50,280
- Fine. Come here.
- Hey, hey, hey.

302
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:51,840
You've been putting ideas
in my sister's head, right?

303
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:53,240
- Samut!
- No!

304
00:33:58,760 --> 00:34:00,560
If you're going to shoot Wayu,
shoot me first.

305
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:02,080
Fahsai?

306
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:04,560
I love him.

307
00:34:12,120 --> 00:34:13,040
Fahsai…

308
00:34:16,239 --> 00:34:18,679
I won't let Wayu
get shot right in front of me.

309
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:27,600
Fahsai, move.

310
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:31,120
Move!

311
00:34:31,199 --> 00:34:34,080
- Samut. No!
- Move!

312
00:34:48,159 --> 00:34:50,120
Samut. Let go.

313
00:34:50,199 --> 00:34:51,600
Let go.

314
00:35:03,680 --> 00:35:06,960
Sir, Mr. Dharn is holding
a press conference.

315
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:12,600
- Yong, take Fahsai and Wayu to hospital.
- Yes, sir?

316
00:35:12,680 --> 00:35:13,800
Yes, sir.

317
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:56,240
I invited everyone here today
because my party committee and I

318
00:35:56,880 --> 00:36:00,200
have carefully decided that we will file
a lawsuit against Mr. Mahasamut

319
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:02,440
for physical and emotional assault,

320
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:04,680
defamation of my honor and dignity,

321
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:08,440
and for misleading the public.

322
00:36:09,200 --> 00:36:11,560
All evidence is now
in the hands of my lawyer.

323
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:16,360
Is this because Ms. Fahsai
has spoken with Mr. Mahasamut

324
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:20,400
and chosen to side with her brother,
which has led to this lawsuit?

325
00:36:20,480 --> 00:36:23,200
Ms. Fahsai and I are good friends.

326
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:24,600
We did nothing improper.

327
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:27,360
And yet I was physically assaulted

328
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:29,360
and publicly criticized.

329
00:36:30,400 --> 00:36:32,040
I gave Mr. Mahasamut time

330
00:36:32,120 --> 00:36:34,720
to reflect on everything that happened.

331
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:36,880
<i>All I asked for was an apology.</i>

332
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:40,000
<i>Are you afraid the issue</i>
<i>will be swept under the rug?</i>

333
00:36:40,080 --> 00:36:42,280
<i>If we hurt someone</i>
<i>when they did nothing wrong,</i>

334
00:36:43,120 --> 00:36:45,440
<i>we should apologize. Isn't that correct?</i>

335
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:48,560
<i>It's basic social courtesy.</i>

336
00:36:49,720 --> 00:36:52,080
<i>And as politicians under public scrutiny,</i>

337
00:36:52,760 --> 00:36:56,520
<i>we should set a good example</i>
<i>for the people. Correct?</i>

338
00:37:06,120 --> 00:37:07,920
This time, you can't avoid it.

339
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:13,200
Call the reporters.

340
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:18,400
Tell them Mahasamut will hold
a press conference tomorrow to apologize.

341
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:20,840
Yes, sir.

342
00:37:35,760 --> 00:37:37,120
You should go home and rest.

343
00:37:40,240 --> 00:37:41,480
I don't feel at ease.

344
00:37:45,240 --> 00:37:48,520
You saw it yourself. The doctor
already wheeled me off for an X-ray,

345
00:37:49,240 --> 00:37:51,600
sent me through this tunnel
and that tunnel.

346
00:37:52,720 --> 00:37:55,600
My liver, kidneys, intestines,
and bones are all still there. I'm fine.

347
00:37:56,480 --> 00:37:57,880
No worries.

348
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:03,360
You've been hurt
because of me again and again.

349
00:38:07,200 --> 00:38:10,200
That's part of being a bodyguard.
Getting hurt is normal.

350
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:20,440
My body hurts,

351
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:22,720
but my heart feels warm.

352
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:32,280
If your brother

353
00:38:32,840 --> 00:38:34,400
hadn't pointed a gun at my head,

354
00:38:35,840 --> 00:38:38,120
I might've gone home daydreaming
that you really loved me.

355
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:54,640
If I hadn't done that,

356
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:57,080
Samut would never have stopped.

357
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:01,800
There goes my dream.

358
00:39:17,840 --> 00:39:19,000
How are you?

359
00:39:19,680 --> 00:39:20,840
Feeling better?

360
00:39:21,680 --> 00:39:24,160
The doctor said
I should stay for two more days,

361
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:25,680
but I'm planning to stay a night.

362
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:29,480
I'm sorry on behalf of my son.

363
00:39:30,440 --> 00:39:32,040
That hot temper of his,

364
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:34,480
he never fixes it.

365
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:38,400
Good thing he came
to his senses because of you.

366
00:39:41,920 --> 00:39:45,320
But there's something else I want to know.

367
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:49,520
What you said, was it true?

368
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:58,200
What do you mean?

369
00:40:00,280 --> 00:40:02,640
It's about what you said,
that you love Wayu.

370
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:06,480
If there's anything to say,
say it directly here.

371
00:40:13,040 --> 00:40:14,240
It's not true, sir.

372
00:40:17,400 --> 00:40:19,560
Ms. Fahsai only said that to help me.

373
00:40:27,560 --> 00:40:29,440
I'm the one who loves her.

374
00:40:38,640 --> 00:40:40,760
That's why I want to do
everything I can to protect her.

375
00:41:15,120 --> 00:41:17,560
You shouldn't have told my father that.

376
00:41:17,640 --> 00:41:19,120
I'm afraid it'll worry him.

377
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:22,000
I didn't want him to misunderstand you.

378
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:24,680
Someone like you

379
00:41:25,480 --> 00:41:27,520
suits a wealthy politician.

380
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:31,720
I'm just a bodyguard.

381
00:41:32,600 --> 00:41:34,720
I may have money, but I have no status.

382
00:41:37,520 --> 00:41:39,120
Can status, money,

383
00:41:39,720 --> 00:41:41,960
and power buy love?

384
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:45,720
For some women, yes.

385
00:41:46,560 --> 00:41:47,800
Not me.

386
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:55,280
Are you saying

387
00:41:56,760 --> 00:41:57,960
you love me?

388
00:41:59,200 --> 00:42:00,440
Hey!

389
00:42:01,640 --> 00:42:04,560
Oh, I'm sorry.

390
00:42:04,640 --> 00:42:06,600
- Nurse. Nurse.
- Hey.

391
00:42:08,720 --> 00:42:09,920
I was teasing you.

392
00:43:00,800 --> 00:43:01,720
This…

393
00:43:04,880 --> 00:43:05,960
is my best medicine.

394
00:43:12,400 --> 00:43:13,320
Hey.

395
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:16,760
Even if you hit me, it doesn't hurt.
The medicine is good.

396
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:21,040
It doesn't hurt. The medicine is too good.

397
00:43:22,240 --> 00:43:23,480
What are you playing at?

398
00:43:26,800 --> 00:43:28,600
Can you not rush home yet?

399
00:43:30,720 --> 00:43:32,360
Stay with me a little longer.

400
00:43:34,280 --> 00:43:35,640
Having you here

401
00:43:36,280 --> 00:43:37,240
feels good.

402
00:44:14,760 --> 00:44:16,520
I don't see any burn marks.

403
00:44:21,240 --> 00:44:23,400
You were stirring up old flames
the other day, weren't you?

404
00:44:27,080 --> 00:44:28,960
Be careful. It might catch fire again.

405
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:30,720
No chance.

406
00:44:33,920 --> 00:44:35,640
She made me 100% sure

407
00:44:37,200 --> 00:44:39,120
I was the foolish one.

408
00:44:41,640 --> 00:44:44,320
Someone who only thinks about herself
with every breath she takes

409
00:44:45,520 --> 00:44:47,000
can never really love anyone.

410
00:44:50,880 --> 00:44:52,600
So, no old flames.

411
00:44:55,680 --> 00:44:57,640
What about that fresh,
cool water named Fahsai?

412
00:44:58,840 --> 00:45:01,280
You're willing to get hurt
and risk your life this much

413
00:45:02,560 --> 00:45:04,320
just to bait the prey?

414
00:45:07,360 --> 00:45:08,520
It worked, didn't it?

415
00:45:10,600 --> 00:45:13,240
Did you see Samut's face when his sister

416
00:45:13,320 --> 00:45:16,160
threw herself in front of a bullet for me?

417
00:45:20,760 --> 00:45:21,920
Damn satisfying.

418
00:45:23,920 --> 00:45:25,200
Is that really all?

419
00:45:31,720 --> 00:45:33,000
Be careful then.

420
00:45:34,560 --> 00:45:36,280
Fresh, cool water

421
00:45:37,080 --> 00:45:39,680
might burn you alive one day.

422
00:45:49,120 --> 00:45:50,400
That was Peeraka.

423
00:45:51,480 --> 00:45:52,560
Not Wayu.

424
00:46:10,240 --> 00:46:12,400
Why are you so tense?

425
00:46:12,480 --> 00:46:14,440
Just follow the script.

426
00:46:14,960 --> 00:46:18,480
Once you're done, bow to the camera.
It won't hurt your pride.

427
00:46:18,560 --> 00:46:20,600
The reporters are our people.

428
00:46:27,080 --> 00:46:28,280
Sir.

429
00:46:49,960 --> 00:46:51,120
How did he get here?

430
00:46:52,800 --> 00:46:54,000
I don't know, sir.

431
00:46:54,840 --> 00:46:58,160
Only our internal team
knew the press conference schedule.

432
00:46:59,760 --> 00:47:00,960
Minister Rakchart is here, sir.

433
00:47:12,080 --> 00:47:14,480
Someone using a burner account
sent an urgent message to our inbox.

434
00:47:14,560 --> 00:47:17,880
They said Mr. Mahasamut is preparing
to apologize privately,

435
00:47:17,960 --> 00:47:20,000
with only his own reporters present.

436
00:47:20,080 --> 00:47:22,280
I checked, and it's true, sir.

437
00:47:27,440 --> 00:47:30,160
Good afternoon, Minister.

438
00:47:32,240 --> 00:47:34,000
Good afternoon, Mr. Dharn.

439
00:47:35,160 --> 00:47:38,040
If you were coming,
you should have told us in advance.

440
00:47:38,120 --> 00:47:40,360
We could've prepared a better welcome.

441
00:47:41,720 --> 00:47:44,720
No need at all.
I should be the one apologizing

442
00:47:44,800 --> 00:47:46,400
for coming so suddenly.

443
00:47:46,480 --> 00:47:49,440
I imagine you may not
have had time to prepare.

444
00:47:51,480 --> 00:47:54,840
I'm here today to show everyone

445
00:47:54,920 --> 00:47:57,680
that the friendship between
our parties remains strong.

446
00:47:59,560 --> 00:48:00,880
Since Mr. Mahasamut is apologizing,

447
00:48:01,640 --> 00:48:03,040
I'm happy to accept it.

448
00:48:03,880 --> 00:48:05,440
The people will see

449
00:48:05,520 --> 00:48:08,160
that their representatives are gentlemen.

450
00:48:08,800 --> 00:48:10,280
When they make a mistake, they admit it.

451
00:48:11,040 --> 00:48:12,760
I also brought reporters with me today.

452
00:48:13,400 --> 00:48:16,480
I hope you and Mr. Mahasamut won't mind.

453
00:48:24,400 --> 00:48:27,960
Bro, the hashtag #FamousPartyMPtoApologize

454
00:48:28,040 --> 00:48:29,600
is trending at number one.

455
00:48:36,480 --> 00:48:38,320
<i>Took him long enough to apologize.</i>

456
00:48:38,400 --> 00:48:40,920
<i>Mr. Dharn's wound</i>
<i>probably healed ages ago.</i>

457
00:48:41,000 --> 00:48:43,800
<i>Only apologizing</i>
<i>because he's about to get sued.</i>

458
00:48:43,880 --> 00:48:46,520
<i>He's an MP and still has no basic decency.</i>

459
00:48:46,600 --> 00:48:48,480
<i>This country is getting harder to live in.</i>

460
00:48:48,560 --> 00:48:51,480
<i>If you're so tough, don't apologize.</i>
<i>Let them sue you.</i>

461
00:48:55,040 --> 00:48:57,760
So satisfying. Everyone's cursing him out.

462
00:48:57,840 --> 00:48:59,240
A cross-party romance,

463
00:48:59,880 --> 00:49:02,120
a full Romeo and Juliet plot like that?

464
00:49:02,880 --> 00:49:05,200
Samut becomes the villain, obviously.

465
00:49:05,840 --> 00:49:10,920
He's going to be humiliated.
Every news outlet is gathered there.

466
00:49:33,680 --> 00:49:36,160
Good afternoon, distinguished guests,

467
00:49:37,160 --> 00:49:38,400
party members,

468
00:49:39,720 --> 00:49:41,920
Mr. Dharn from Namjai Thai Party,

469
00:49:43,280 --> 00:49:44,760
members of the press,

470
00:49:45,320 --> 00:49:47,480
and all Thai citizens.

471
00:49:48,800 --> 00:49:53,160
Today, our party has arranged this press
conference to apologize to Mr. Dharn.

472
00:49:54,560 --> 00:49:55,800
Alright.

473
00:50:03,880 --> 00:50:04,920
Good afternoon,

474
00:50:05,000 --> 00:50:09,440
and thank you all for taking the time
to attend today's press conference.

475
00:50:11,160 --> 00:50:15,720
Since the day someone
released a video clip showing me

476
00:50:16,720 --> 00:50:18,720
using violence against Mr. Dharn,

477
00:50:22,280 --> 00:50:25,400
I have become a defendant
in the court of public opinion.

478
00:50:31,280 --> 00:50:34,080
I haven't had the chance
to explain what happened.

479
00:50:34,680 --> 00:50:36,160
But today is a good day

480
00:50:37,840 --> 00:50:40,280
for me to clarify the facts

481
00:50:40,360 --> 00:50:43,280
about what happened that day,
so everyone will know the truth.

482
00:50:46,840 --> 00:50:50,000
However, I would like
to begin with this video clip.

483
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:06,320
- Whose clip is this?
- Call them first.

484
00:51:12,240 --> 00:51:13,200
Oh no.

485
00:51:13,840 --> 00:51:16,000
What the hell is this?

486
00:51:31,280 --> 00:51:32,920
<i>I came to ask for help.</i>

487
00:51:33,000 --> 00:51:35,640
<i>He's powerful, and I was scared.</i>

488
00:51:35,720 --> 00:51:38,640
<i>He told me</i>
<i>he would get me a job in the party.</i>

489
00:51:40,080 --> 00:51:42,600
<i>Then he called me to a meeting at a hotel.</i>

490
00:51:43,800 --> 00:51:44,800
<i>In the end,</i>

491
00:51:44,880 --> 00:51:47,040
<i>he assaulted me</i>

492
00:51:47,120 --> 00:51:50,640
<i>and threatened me not to tell anyone.</i>

493
00:51:50,720 --> 00:51:51,800
Sam.

494
00:51:52,440 --> 00:51:53,600
Check if that clip is real.

495
00:51:53,680 --> 00:51:55,200
Mr. Dharn?

496
00:51:56,600 --> 00:51:58,240
This is big.

497
00:52:18,440 --> 00:52:22,760
If anyone doubts
whether this video clip has been edited,

498
00:52:24,600 --> 00:52:26,680
please feel free to have it examined.

499
00:52:29,520 --> 00:52:31,120
If I weren't certain,

500
00:52:31,960 --> 00:52:35,000
I would never speak
about it publicly like this.

501
00:52:38,360 --> 00:52:39,240
And that is

502
00:52:39,880 --> 00:52:42,920
why I lost control of myself that day,

503
00:52:47,160 --> 00:52:50,000
when I found out Mr. Dharn

504
00:52:50,080 --> 00:52:53,360
had secretly arranged to meet my sister.

505
00:52:53,960 --> 00:52:55,360
So you already knew, Mr. Samut?

506
00:52:55,440 --> 00:52:57,400
Is that why you were so angry?

507
00:52:57,480 --> 00:53:00,120
Did anything happen to Ms. Fahsai?

508
00:53:01,040 --> 00:53:04,480
Even though nothing this terrible
happened to my sister,

509
00:53:05,400 --> 00:53:06,800
as her brother,

510
00:53:08,760 --> 00:53:09,880
I can't let it happen.

511
00:53:12,320 --> 00:53:13,360
Yes,

512
00:53:14,600 --> 00:53:16,280
I may have acted rashly,

513
00:53:17,880 --> 00:53:20,240
and for that, I apologize to the public.

514
00:53:25,680 --> 00:53:28,920
But if I had not stood up
to protect my sister,

515
00:53:29,920 --> 00:53:32,120
who could guarantee that he wouldn't do

516
00:53:32,200 --> 00:53:33,640
the same thing to my sister

517
00:53:33,720 --> 00:53:35,440
as he did to the victim in this clip?

518
00:53:36,320 --> 00:53:39,000
Mr. Dharn, is the man
in the clip really you?

519
00:53:39,080 --> 00:53:41,480
- Mr. Dharn.
- Please answer.

520
00:53:41,560 --> 00:53:43,640
- Mr. Dharn.
- Please answer.

521
00:53:46,000 --> 00:53:49,480
- Mr. Dharn.
- Please answer the question.

522
00:53:49,560 --> 00:53:50,720
Please don't walk away.

523
00:54:02,200 --> 00:54:04,920
<i>Aniyo!</i>

524
00:54:05,880 --> 00:54:07,920
I can't accept this. It can't be true.

525
00:54:08,680 --> 00:54:12,320
A perfect gentleman like Mr. Dharn

526
00:54:12,920 --> 00:54:15,000
shouldn't have done something like this.

527
00:54:23,200 --> 00:54:26,760
So how did you know
the man behind that mask was Dharn?

528
00:54:32,440 --> 00:54:34,760
<i>My party committee and I</i>

529
00:54:34,840 --> 00:54:37,760
<i>have carefully decided that we will file</i>
<i>a lawsuit against Mr. Mahasamut</i>

530
00:54:38,360 --> 00:54:40,280
<i>for physical and emotional assault,</i>

531
00:54:40,880 --> 00:54:43,920
- <i>defamation…</i>
- Who's that guy in glasses behind Dharn?

532
00:54:44,000 --> 00:54:46,000
He looks familiar.

533
00:54:46,720 --> 00:54:47,800
Mr. Rewat.

534
00:54:48,520 --> 00:54:51,440
He's one of Thailand's
major rubber exporters.

535
00:54:52,040 --> 00:54:54,080
He rarely appears in public,

536
00:54:54,160 --> 00:54:57,520
but insiders know
he's a key backer of Dharn

537
00:54:57,600 --> 00:54:58,960
and Namjai Thai Party.

538
00:55:00,000 --> 00:55:02,080
Didn't he once recommend
a VIP guest to us?

539
00:55:04,080 --> 00:55:05,120
Yes, Boss.

540
00:55:20,120 --> 00:55:23,640
So Rewat's VIP guest really was Dharn.

541
00:55:26,840 --> 00:55:29,640
He meant to come after me,
but ended up sleeping with my girl?

542
00:55:29,720 --> 00:55:32,600
But Mr. Dharn
only used the service once, sir.

543
00:55:32,680 --> 00:55:34,160
I searched everything.

544
00:55:34,240 --> 00:55:35,920
This is the only clip.

545
00:55:36,000 --> 00:55:37,520
Once is more than enough.

546
00:55:37,600 --> 00:55:41,240
But all VVIP information
has to remain confidential.

547
00:55:41,320 --> 00:55:44,720
Every guest trusts us because of that.

548
00:55:44,800 --> 00:55:46,200
In Mr. Dharn's case,

549
00:55:46,280 --> 00:55:48,320
we even arranged for the girl
to be sent to the hotel.

550
00:55:48,400 --> 00:55:50,160
If we expose this…

551
00:55:50,240 --> 00:55:53,640
I'm not stupid enough
to let anyone trace this back to us.

552
00:56:00,960 --> 00:56:02,360
Call this girl in.

553
00:56:04,320 --> 00:56:07,840
Once I got the girl, I staged the video

554
00:56:09,840 --> 00:56:11,840
and had her claim

555
00:56:12,560 --> 00:56:14,040
that Dharn tricked her.

556
00:56:14,960 --> 00:56:17,680
Tossed her some money and sent her abroad.

557
00:56:18,840 --> 00:56:20,080
That's all it took.

558
00:56:21,160 --> 00:56:24,240
Then why didn't you tell me earlier?

559
00:56:24,320 --> 00:56:26,560
You let me stress over this for so long.

560
00:56:30,840 --> 00:56:34,120
At first, I didn't want to go this far.

561
00:56:37,760 --> 00:56:38,840
But he asked for it.

562
00:56:43,760 --> 00:56:46,320
By now, his clip
must be all over social media.

563
00:56:51,080 --> 00:56:52,680
He picked the wrong person

564
00:56:53,360 --> 00:56:54,640
to mess with.

565
00:56:57,160 --> 00:56:59,440
This is how you lose
your place in the world.

566
00:57:02,120 --> 00:57:04,240
Ms. Fahsai.

567
00:57:04,840 --> 00:57:08,280
Mr. Dharn announced his resignation
from the party. He's quitting politics.

568
00:57:09,840 --> 00:57:11,120
<i>Seulpeoyo.</i>

569
00:57:11,880 --> 00:57:13,800
I'm so sad.

570
00:57:15,160 --> 00:57:19,120
Ms. Fahsai, do you think
that clip was real?

571
00:57:22,200 --> 00:57:24,280
But when we worked together,

572
00:57:24,360 --> 00:57:26,960
I really thought he genuinely
wanted to work for society.

573
00:57:27,040 --> 00:57:28,720
Yes, that's true.

574
00:57:31,120 --> 00:57:32,960
People don't have only one side.

575
00:57:35,640 --> 00:57:37,840
He may have wanted you
to see only the good side of him.

576
00:57:40,240 --> 00:57:42,200
But it was just one mistake.

577
00:57:44,080 --> 00:57:46,440
All of us have made mistakes.

578
00:57:56,680 --> 00:57:57,720
Samut is probably…

579
00:58:00,680 --> 00:58:01,840
the same.

580
00:58:09,040 --> 00:58:11,240
And you believe that?

581
00:58:25,320 --> 00:58:27,280
You think just because
someone made one mistake,

582
00:58:29,480 --> 00:58:31,120
they won't make another?

583
00:58:35,240 --> 00:58:36,760
One single mistake

584
00:58:39,840 --> 00:58:42,720
can destroy someone else's entire life.

585
00:59:02,360 --> 00:59:03,320
So what is it?

586
00:59:04,720 --> 00:59:06,120
Do you feel sorry for Mr. Dharn?

587
00:59:07,600 --> 00:59:09,400
Are you disappointed?

588
00:59:10,280 --> 00:59:11,240
Or heartbroken?

589
00:59:19,600 --> 00:59:22,320
Tell me. What do you feel?

590
00:59:23,160 --> 00:59:24,880
Step back. Hey.

591
00:59:27,520 --> 00:59:28,800
Let go.

592
00:59:30,680 --> 00:59:31,840
I said let go.

593
00:59:36,200 --> 00:59:38,440
Hey. Let go!

594
00:59:47,320 --> 00:59:48,680
Gosh.

595
01:00:02,080 --> 01:00:03,240
No matter what happens,

596
01:00:04,800 --> 01:00:07,040
I'll always be right here,
holding your hand.

597
01:00:08,440 --> 01:00:12,120
As her father, I would like
to invite everyone here

598
01:00:12,200 --> 01:00:15,280
to my daughter's wedding
with Mr. Wayu Buranachat.

599
01:00:22,120 --> 01:00:23,080
Damn it!

600
01:00:23,160 --> 01:00:27,400
I'll never let this wedding happen.

601
01:00:30,240 --> 01:00:31,800
If you love me,

602
01:00:31,880 --> 01:00:33,680
can I ask you something?

603
01:00:33,760 --> 01:00:35,320
Leave them.

604
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:39,320
Let's go somewhere far away
and start a simple life together.

605
01:00:41,760 --> 01:00:45,920
‪SPECIAL THANKS

606
01:01:36,080 --> 01:01:38,720
Subtitle translation by:
Panuwat Baikeawon
